The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                    NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Chennai, Nov. 10: Forty-two people have died in landslides caused by torrential rain in Nilgiris district of Tamil Nadu. On Monday night 29 people were crushed to death in their homes near Ooty. During the last three days, 100 landslides have occurred across the district that have also cut off traffic to hill towns like Ooty and Conoor.                   
	 London (PTI): A Briton has been sentenced to a minimum 18 years in prison for the racially-aggravated murder of Indian Navy officer Kunal Mohanty. Christopher Miller, 25, had knifed 30-year-old Mohanty in the neck as he walked to a restaurant with his friends in Glasgow in March this year.                   
	 London (PTI): At least 10 students, including six of Indian origin, were injured in two separate incidents after a gang of white and black youths attacked Asian Muslim students at the City University in north London last week.                  
	 Shahdol, MP (PTI): A trade union leader has pulled a Sholay stunt to force South Eastern Coalfield to revoke his transfer. Manulal Gujjar climbed atop a cellphone tower and got down after nine hours when assured he would not be shifted.                                                                                                                                                 
